{"updated_at": "2012-10-27T17:54:14Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-10-27T17:54:14Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9837931", "id": 9837931, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8016", "issue_id": 8016, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "id": 26328, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "body": "Actually, I think the same could be achieved with a custom responder in your application, by overriding `json_resource_errors`. I'm not sure that should be added by default in `respond_with`, since there are so many other options that can be given to `json/xml` methods either in success or failure scenarios, and we definitely don't want `respond_with` to know all of them.\r\n\r\nThat said, I'm -1 on this one. Thanks @sidonath for your contribution.", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f6aabd3543c15100aed5"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8016#issuecomment-9837931"}
